# Theme tokens only ‚Äî no hardcoded hex in components

Use the shared theme layer for all UI colors. Do **not** drop raw hex colors into components.

**See also:** semantic tokens below and `theme/tokens.ts` for the single source of truth.

## Semantic text tokens (dark mode readable)

Use these so every screen is readable in dark mode without squinting:

- **textPrimary** ‚Äî Titles, section headers (Description, Book Information), row values, nav/back. Near-white in dark (not pure white).
- **textSecondary** ‚Äî Body text, row labels (Publisher, ISBN), secondary copy. Clearly readable in dark (not washed out).
- **textTertiary** ‚Äî Rare; slightly de‚Äëemphasized vs secondary (e.g. read date).
- **textMuted** ‚Äî **Only** for hints and placeholders (e.g. "No description available", input placeholder). **Not** for section labels like "Description" or "Book Information".
- **divider** ‚Äî Section dividers; subtle but visible in dark (~20‚Äì30% opacity). Use for `borderTopColor` / `borderBottomColor` on section boundaries.
- **surface / surface2 / background** ‚Äî Use semantic names; no gray hex.

## Contrast rules in components

1. **Section headers** (e.g. "Description", "Book Information", "From Scan") ‚Üí **textPrimary** or strong secondary. Never muted.
2. **Body text** ‚Üí **textSecondary**.
3. **Placeholder / empty state** (e.g. "No description available") ‚Üí **textMuted**.
4. **Row labels** (Publisher, ISBN, etc.) ‚Üí **textSecondary**.
5. **Row values** ‚Üí **textPrimary**.
6. **Dividers** ‚Üí **divider** (or separator); avoid hairline-only if invisible in dark.

## Token layer (use via `useTheme()` ‚Üí `t.colors`)

- **colors.bg** ‚Äî screen / scroll background
- **colors.surface** / **surface2** ‚Äî headers, cards, modals, chips, inputs
- **colors.textPrimary** ‚Äî primary text (prefer over `text` for new code)
- **colors.textSecondary** ‚Äî secondary text, row labels
- **colors.textMuted** ‚Äî hints, placeholders only
- **colors.divider** ‚Äî section dividers (visible in dark)
- **colors.border** ‚Äî subtle outlines
- **colors.primary** / **primaryText** ‚Äî primary CTAs; **primaryText** = text on accent buttons only (not header bar text; use textPrimary for header/back)
- **colors.accent** / **accent2** ‚Äî progress, tab active
- **colors.danger** ‚Äî destructive actions

## Rules

1. **Borders / dividers** ‚Üí `t.colors.divider` or `t.colors.border`
2. **Surfaces** ‚Üí `t.colors.surface` or `t.colors.surface2` or `t.colors.bg`
3. **Text** ‚Üí `t.colors.textPrimary` | `textSecondary` | `textMuted` (choose by hierarchy above)
4. **No raw hex** in component JSX or style objects (except inside `theme/tokens.ts`).

## Dark mode audit checklist (Cursor)

When touching UI, search and fix:

1. **Hardcoded grays** ‚Äî `#999`, `#AAA`, `#718096`, `#a0aec0`, `#505050`, `rgba(0,0,0,0.4)` in components ‚Üí replace with semantic tokens (`textPrimary`, `textSecondary`, `textMuted`, `divider`).
2. **placeholderTextColor** ‚Äî must use `t.colors.textMuted` (or theme equivalent); never a hex that‚Äôs too close to background in dark.
3. **Text same color as surfaces** ‚Äî ensure text uses textPrimary/textSecondary so it‚Äôs not invisible on surface/bg.
4. **Section labels** ‚Äî any "Description", "Book Information", row header using muted ‚Üí change to textPrimary or textSecondary.

Acceptance: In dark mode, every label and value on Book Details and Settings is readable without squinting; dividers are subtle but visible.
